This paper focuses on the integration of pre-trained language models (LMs) into neural machine translation (NMT), which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel framework that involves techniques such as dynamic switching gates and learning pace adjustment, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions experiments with large datasets, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) subcategories.
